Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve and peel the @red onion{1%unit}, then cut each half into 3 wedges.

Trim the @butternut squash{1%unit}, halve lengthways, then scoop out the seeds
(peel first if you prefer). Cut into 2cm chunks.

Pop the butternut and onion onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{2%tbsp}
and sprinkle over the @roasted spice and herb blend{1%sachet}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast the veg on the top shelf until golden and cooked
through, ~{25-30%mins}.

When there's 10 mins of roasting time left, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}
to the baking tray. Pop into the oven and roast until golden, ~{8-10%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Meanwhile, tear the @ciabatta{1%unit} into roughly 2cm chunks. Pop the ciabatta
onto another baking tray in a single layer.

Drizzle with @olive oil{}(for the croutons), season with salt and pepper and
toss to coat well. Add the @chopped kale{100%g} to the other side of tray, drizzle
with @olive oil{}(for the kale), season with salt and pepper and toss to coat.
Set aside for now.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @cider vinegar{30%ml}, @sugar{2%tsp} and olive
oil for the dressing. Season with salt and pepper and set your dressing aside.

In another small bowl, combine the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} with half
the @Zhoug style paste{45%g}. Set aside.

Drain and rinse the @butter beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

When there is about 7-8 mins of veg roasting time remaining, pop the crouton
and kale tray onto the middle shelf of your oven and bake until golden and
the kale is crispy, ~{7-8%mins}.

Meanwhile, pop a medium #saucepan{} on medium heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the butter beans, then stir in the remaining zhoug (add less if
you prefer things milder). Cook until warmed through, ~{2-3%mins}, then remove
from the heat.

When everything's ready, add the roasted veg, butter beans and croutons to the
dressing bowl.

Crumble in the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} and toss together. Taste and
add more salt and pepper if needed.

Share the warm salad out between your #serving bowls{} and drizzle over the
zhoug yoghurt to finish.

Enjoy!